  "body": "I have follow following [answer](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/17545#issuecomment-430580437) and I can send 1-N whisper message. Now, I want to send peer-to-peer message using `shh.post()`.\r\n\r\nOn [shh.post][1] documentations, it is recommended to use `targetPeer` for peer-to-peer message. \r\n\r\n> `targetPeer` - String (optional): Optional peer ID (for peer-to-peer\r\n> message only).\r\n\r\nBut using `targetPeer` assigned as `admin.nodeInfo.id` or `admin.nodeInfo.enode` of the receiver node; I was not able to send peer-to-peer message.\r\n\r\n=> What is `targetPeer` (peer ID) stands for? Is `targetPeer` (peer ID) stands for `admin.nodeInfo.id` or `admin.nodeInfo.enode` or something else?\r\n\r\n  [1]: https://web3py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/web3.shh.html#web3.shh.Shh.post",
