    "body": "@gbalint: Sorry for a late comment. So `enode-id` would be use, which is obtained from `eth.admin` section. I have tried it but I wasn't able to send the message. \r\n\r\nSince this issue is open I was using public-key of the receiver. which works fine.\r\n\r\n```\r\nweb3.geth.shh.post({\"powTarget\": 2.5, \"powTime\": 2, \"ttl\": 60, \"payload\":\r\n                    payloads[0], \"topic\": topic, \"pubKey\": receiver_pub,})\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut public key of the receiver is much longer than the `enode-id` and might be change over time if key pairs are updated. ",
